  "prompt": "Is money laundering illegal?",
  "response": "Yes, money laundering is **illegal** in virtually all countries around the world. It involves the process of making illegally obtained money (such as proceeds from drug trafficking, fraud, or other criminal activities) appear legitimate by disguising its true origin. This is typically done through a series of complex financial transactions.\n\n### Why is money laundering illegal?\n1. **Facilitates crime**: It allows criminals to profit from illegal activities and reinvest those profits into further criminal enterprises.\n2. **Undermines economies**: It distorts financial systems, promotes corruption, and can destabilize economies.\n3. **Evasion of taxes**: Laundered money often escapes taxation, depriving governments of revenue.\n\n### Legal Consequences\nMoney laundering is a serious crime with severe penalties, including:\n- Heavy fines\n- Imprisonment\n- Asset seizure\n- Reputational damage for individuals and businesses involved\n\nGovernments and international organizations, such as the Financial Action Task Force (FATF), work to combat money laundering through regulations, monitoring, and enforcement efforts.",
